HEADWORD: Diabolo
<hw>Di*ab"o*lo</hw> <pr>(d⟦icr⟧*⟦acr⟧b"⟦osl⟧*l⟦omac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>An old game or sport (revived under this name)
consisting in whirling on a string, fastened to two sticks, a small
somewhat spool-shaped object (called the <xex>diabolo</xex>) so as to
balance it on a string, toss it in the air and catch it, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diacatholicon</ent>⟦br⟧
